# Installation Guide

## Prerequisites

### Build Requirements

- Go 1.21 or later
- Git
- Make
- Platform-specific:
  - **macOS**: Xcode Command Line Tools
  - **Windows**: Visual Studio Build Tools or MinGW-w64
  - **Linux**: GCC, build-essential

### Runtime Requirements

- Root/Administrator privileges (for system configuration)
- Network access to After Dark Systems APIs
- DarkAPI.io API key

## Building from Source

### Clone and Build

```bash
git clone https://github.com/afterdarksys/afterdark-darkd.git
cd afterdark-darkd

# Download dependencies
make deps

# Build all binaries
make build

# Run tests
make test
```

### Cross-Platform Builds

```bash
# Build for all supported platforms
make build-all

# Binaries output to dist/
ls dist/
```

## Installation

### macOS

```bash
# Install binaries
sudo make install

# Create directories
sudo mkdir -p /etc/afterdark /var/lib/afterdark /var/log/afterdark /var/run/afterdark

# Copy configuration
sudo cp configs/darkd.yaml.example /etc/afterdark/darkd.yaml

# Edit configuration
sudo vim /etc/afterdark/darkd.yaml

# Install launchd service
sudo cp scripts/service/launchd/com.afterdarksys.darkd.plist /Library/LaunchDaemons/
sudo launchctl load /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.afterdarksys.darkd.plist

# Start service
sudo launchctl start com.afterdarksys.darkd
```

### Linux (systemd)

```bash
# Install binaries
sudo make install

# Create directories
sudo mkdir -p /etc/afterdark /var/lib/afterdark /var/log/afterdark /var/run/afterdark

# Copy configuration
sudo cp configs/darkd.yaml.example /etc/afterdark/darkd.yaml

# Edit configuration
sudo vim /etc/afterdark/darkd.yaml

# Install systemd service
sudo cp scripts/service/systemd/afterdark-darkd.service /etc/systemd/system/
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable afterdark-darkd
sudo systemctl start afterdark-darkd

# Check status
sudo systemctl status afterdark-darkd
```

### Windows

```powershell
# Run as Administrator

# Create directories
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark" -Force
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark\data" -Force
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark\logs" -Force

# Copy binaries
Copy-Item afterdark-darkd.exe "C:\Program Files\AfterDark\"
Copy-Item afterdark-darkdadm.exe "C:\Program Files\AfterDark\"
Copy-Item darkapi.exe "C:\Program Files\AfterDark\"

# Copy configuration
Copy-Item configs\darkd.yaml.example "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark\darkd.yaml"

# Edit configuration
notepad "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark\darkd.yaml"

# Install as Windows service
sc.exe create "AfterDarkDarkD" binPath= "C:\Program Files\AfterDark\afterdark-darkd.exe --config C:\ProgramData\AfterDark\darkd.yaml" start= auto
sc.exe description "AfterDarkDarkD" "After Dark Systems Endpoint Security Daemon"

# Start service
sc.exe start AfterDarkDarkD
```

## Configuration

### Minimal Configuration

```yaml
daemon:
  log_level: info
  data_dir: /var/lib/afterdark
  pid_file: /var/run/afterdark/darkd.pid

api:
  darkapi:
    url: https://api.darkapi.io
    api_key: ${DARKAPI_API_KEY}

services:
  patch_monitor:
    enabled: true
  threat_intel:
    enabled: true
  network_monitor:
    enabled: true
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `DARKAPI_API_KEY` | DarkAPI.io API key |
| `AFTERDARK_CONFIG` | Override config file path |
| `AFTERDARK_LOG_LEVEL` | Override log level |

### API Key Setup

1. Log in to https://console.darkapi.io
2. Navigate to API Keys
3. Create a new key with "Endpoint Agent" permissions
4. Set the environment variable or add to config

## Verification

### Check Daemon Status

```bash
# Linux/macOS
afterdark-darkdadm status

# Windows
& "C:\Program Files\AfterDark\afterdark-darkdadm.exe" status
```

### Check User CLI

```bash
darkapi status
```

### View Logs

```bash
# Linux/macOS
tail -f /var/log/afterdark/darkd.log

# Windows
Get-Content "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark\logs\darkd.log" -Wait
```

## Automated Deployment

### Ansible

```bash
cd deployments/ansible

# Edit inventory
vim inventory/hosts.yml

# Run playbook
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/deploy.yml
```

### Terraform

```bash
cd deployments/terraform/aws

# Initialize
terraform init

# Plan
terraform plan -var="darkapi_key=$DARKAPI_API_KEY"

# Apply
terraform apply -var="darkapi_key=$DARKAPI_API_KEY"
```

## Uninstallation

### macOS

```bash
sudo launchctl stop com.afterdarksys.darkd
sudo launchctl unload /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.afterdarksys.darkd.plist
sudo rm /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.afterdarksys.darkd.plist
sudo rm /usr/local/bin/afterdark-darkd /usr/local/bin/afterdark-darkdadm /usr/local/bin/darkapi
sudo rm -rf /etc/afterdark /var/lib/afterdark /var/log/afterdark
```

### Linux

```bash
sudo systemctl stop afterdark-darkd
sudo systemctl disable afterdark-darkd
sudo rm /etc/systemd/system/afterdark-darkd.service
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo rm /usr/local/bin/afterdark-darkd /usr/local/bin/afterdark-darkdadm /usr/local/bin/darkapi
sudo rm -rf /etc/afterdark /var/lib/afterdark /var/log/afterdark
```

### Windows

```powershell
sc.exe stop AfterDarkDarkD
sc.exe delete AfterDarkDarkD
Remove-Item -Recurse "C:\Program Files\AfterDark"
Remove-Item -Recurse "C:\ProgramData\AfterDark"
```

## Troubleshooting

### Daemon Won't Start

1. Check configuration: `afterdark-darkd --config /etc/afterdark/darkd.yaml --validate`
2. Check permissions on data directories
3. Check API key is set correctly
4. Review logs for errors

### No Threat Data

1. Verify API key has correct permissions
2. Check network connectivity to api.darkapi.io
3. Run manual sync: `afterdark-darkdadm threats sync`

### Patch Scan Fails

1. Ensure running with root/admin privileges
2. Check platform-specific tools are available (softwareupdate, wuauclt, apt)

